Description: Fragment from shoulder of pottery transport amphora; outside fired light cream, Munsell 10YR 8/2 (very pale brown); large pre-firing graffito on outside. Hard, fine, red porous clay, Munsell 2.5YR 6/6 (light red); highly micaceous (silver mica); layers of clay flaking off on inside.
Curator's comments: Possibly part of the same vessel as 2010,5002.29 (but does not join).
Bibliographic references: Weber 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus anderen ägyptischen Fundorten (TD 342)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.114, p.115, p.128, p.129, p.225, pl.67)
Acquisition notes: Found unregistered in the Department in 2010, in a box with other sherds from Tell Dafana.
